mdbook.md
     1тЖТ# mdBook-specific features
     2тЖТ
     3тЖТ## Hiding code lines
     4тЖТ
     5тЖТThere is a feature in mdBook that lets you hide code lines by prepending them with a specific prefix.
     6тЖТ
     7тЖТFor the Rust language, you can prefix lines with `# ` (`#` followed by a space) to hide them [like you would with Rustdoc][rustdoc-hide].
     8тЖТThis prefix can be escaped with `##` to prevent the hiding of a line that should begin with the literal string `# ` (see [Rustdoc's docs][rustdoc-hide] for more details)
     9тЖТ
    10тЖТ[rustdoc-hide]: https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/rustdoc/write-documentation/documentation-tests.html#hiding-portions-of-the-example
    11тЖТ
    12тЖТ```bash
    13тЖТ# fn main() {
    14тЖТ    let x = 5;
    15тЖТ    let y = 6;
    16тЖТ
    17тЖТ    println!("{}", x + y);
    18тЖТ# }
    19тЖТ```
    20тЖТ
    21тЖТWill render as
    22тЖТ
    23тЖТ```rust
    24тЖТ# fn main() {
    25тЖТ    let x = 5;
    26тЖТ    let y = 6;
    27тЖТ
    28тЖТ    println!("{}", x + y);
    29тЖТ# }
    30тЖТ```
    31тЖТ
    32тЖТWhen you tap or hover the mouse over the code block, there will be an eyeball icon (<i class="fa fa-eye"></i>) which will toggle the visibility of the hidden lines.
    33тЖТ
    34тЖТBy default, this only works for code examples that are annotated with `rust`.
    35тЖТHowever, you can define custom prefixes for other languages by adding a new line-hiding prefix in your `book.toml` with the language name and prefix character(s):
    36тЖТ
    37тЖТ```toml
    38тЖТ[output.html.code.hidelines]
    39тЖТpython = "~"
    40тЖТ```
    41тЖТ
    42тЖТThe prefix will hide any lines that begin with the given prefix. With the python prefix shown above, this:
    43тЖТ
    44тЖТ```bash
    45тЖТ~hidden()
    46тЖТnothidden():
    47тЖТ~    hidden()
    48тЖТ    ~hidden()
    49тЖТ    nothidden()
    50тЖТ```
    51тЖТ
    52тЖТwill render as
    53тЖТ
    54тЖТ```python
    55тЖТ~hidden()
    56тЖТnothidden():
    57тЖТ~    hidden()
    58тЖТ    ~hidden()
    59тЖТ    nothidden()
    60тЖТ```
    61тЖТ
    62тЖТThis behavior can be overridden locally with a different prefix. This has the same effect as above:
    63тЖТ
    64тЖТ~~~markdown
    65тЖТ```python,hidelines=!!!
    66тЖТ!!!hidden()
    67тЖТnothidden():
    68тЖТ!!!    hidden()
    69тЖТ    !!!hidden()
    70тЖТ    nothidden()
    71тЖТ```
    72тЖТ~~~
    73тЖТ
